Default to hipBLASLt as the BLAS backend on gfx1100

On gfx1100 (Radeon RX 7900 XTX) torch defaults to rocBLAS for GEMM, and the
rocBLAS shipped in openRuyi has no fp16 GEMM Tensile solution for some problem
shapes (e.g. an N=10 addmm from a small nn.Linear under AMP), failing with:

  RuntimeError: CUDA error: HIPBLAS_STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR when calling
  rocblas_gemm_ex(..., rocblas_datatype_f16_r, ...)

fp32/bf16 GEMM and fp16 square matmul are fine; only fp16 GEMM at those shapes
breaks.  hipBLASLt handles every shape, and forcing it
(TORCH_BLAS_PREFER_HIPBLASLT=1) makes the failure disappear.

The default backend is chosen in Context::blasPreferredBackend(), which prefers
hipBLASLt only for archs in CUDAHooks::getHipblasltPreferredArchs().  Upstream
lists gfx1100/gfx1101 only as *supported* (getHipblasltSupportedArchs), never as
*preferred*, so consumer RDNA3 defaults to the broken rocBLAS path.  Add
gfx1100/gfx1101 to the preferred list so hipBLASLt becomes the default; the
existing supported-arch check still passes (gfx1100 is already supported), so the
backend is not overridden back to rocBLAS.

diff --git a/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp b/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp
index 03a3a97..d01ca21 100644
--- a/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp
+++ b/aten/src/ATen/cuda/detail/CUDAHooks.cpp
@@ -554,6 +554,11 @@ bool CUDAHooks::isGPUArch(const std::vector<std::string>& archs, DeviceIndex dev
 const std::vector<std::string>& CUDAHooks::getHipblasltPreferredArchs() const {
   static const std::vector<std::string> archs = {
     "gfx90a", "gfx942",
+    // openRuyi: gfx1100/gfx1101 are only "supported" upstream, not "preferred",
+    // so torch defaults to rocBLAS on these consumer RDNA3 cards -- but the rocBLAS
+    // shipped here has no fp16 GEMM Tensile solution for some shapes on gfx1100
+    // (HIPBLAS_STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR).  Prefer hipBLASLt, which handles all shapes.
+    "gfx1100", "gfx1101",
 #if ROCM_VERSION >= 60400
     "gfx1200", "gfx1201",
 #endif
